caption.text: This is how I remember America. When I was an exchange student, I lived 10 mins away from Starbucks. For me, it's not only a coffee shop but also a place to share happiness with my family, hang out with my friends, and even a place to have "me time" with their great free wifi. Sunday was my favorite day because my family will do a coffee run there before church. My 4 years old brother loves Starbucks a lot. One day, he was sleeping in the car and told my mom that he wanted a kids hot choco but his eyes were not even open. Whenever I missed the school bus and get a ride from my parent, we'll do Starbucks run first. I am late anyway. The worst day, the day when I have to left my house for Indonesia, I did twice Starbucks run. After say goodbye to my best friend in the morning, and before I left the town. Man, that day was horrible but their coffe did cheer me up a little bit. Because I know, whenever I miss the state, I can just run to Starbucks in Indonesia and order a coffe with the same taste that will remind me about my whole journey. Thankyou Starbucks!!
